<br>
<br>
&lt;&lt;I did think about using the kyu/dan terminology for Bjond (he's a monk), but I didn't think anyone would get it if I said I was 28th kyu, which would mean 22nd level. Kyu counts down to 1, which is just before the 1st dan rank, which then count back up.&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
When I played a monk, I used &quot;kyu&quot; as a direct synonym for &quot;level,&quot; so when I said I was &quot;28th kyu,&quot; I meant 28th level.  You're right, though, that it ought to count backwards from 50 to 1.  But I figured nobody else would do the subtraction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1>Firiona Vie General Chat</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  